Ibadan- Oyo State first lady, Mrs. Taminiomini Olufunke Makinde has on Tuesday called on women across the State to always take good care of their health. Mrs. Makinde always encouraged the women to always go for periodic medical check-up to confirm their health status maintained that health is wealth. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! The State first lady, who was ably represented by the State Commissioner for women and social Inclusion, Alhaja Faosat Ajoke Saani at the End of the Year get together event with women across the State. The event according to the State first lady is meant to celebrate, encourage and share the joy of the season with our women across the state. Delta Exco Approves Construction Of 13 Roads, Flyover Makinde Harps On Zero Tolerance For Corruption, Inaugurates State’s Agency The event, which was a gathering of all the Local Government Chairpersons, the Local Government Women Leaders, Ward Women Leaders and Women from the Sixty- Eight (68) Local Government and Local Council Development Areas of the State as well as women from religious and political groups. She said, “women play several roles in different positions which are demanding thus, I want to encourage us to take good care of ourselves and our health. “I want to encourage us to endeavor to go for regular medical check-ups such as blood sugar level test, blood pressure monitoring, breast and cervical cancer screening. We should create time to engage in physical exercise, because it is only when we are healthy that we can effectively play our roles as wives to our husbands, mother’s to our children and alsoo contribute to our various communities efficiently. “As mothers in the home, I want to remind you that, this is the time to be more dedicated to the upkeep and welfare of your children. Mrs. Makinde stressed. The event, featured cash and food items distributions to all the women at the event. Mrs. Omirinade Jelilat a beneficiary and wife of the Asabari LCDA who spoke on behalf of others, commended the State Governor Engr. Seyi Makinde and his wife for thier kind gesture by given out the cash and other various food items. She also applauded Mrs. Makinde for celebrating with women during this festive season. Also at the event is the State Commissioner for Special Duty, Mrs. Funmilayo Orisadeyi, Permanent Secretary to the Ministry of Women Affairs and social Inclusion Mrs. Christianah Abioye among others. SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION